<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-155-246 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 784 977</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE: Work-Group Computing Report  May 13 1991 v2 n51 p44(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ada market: expected to regain momentum.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Focused Ada Research Corp. (Reports).andO;Topic:     ADAMarket AnalysisGrowthOutlookReports.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>After a disappointing year, Ada is beginning to regain momentum in 1991 andshould achieve about a 20 percent growth rate in 1992, according to FocusedAda Research Corp. (FAR), a market research company with headquarters here.andM;Ada is a programming language and used by the Department of Defense.andM;&quot;1990 was a tough year for most Ada vendors,&quot; said David Dikel, president ofFAR.andP;  &quot;But with visibility given `high tech' systems during the Gulf War, ageneral loosening of defense dollars, and ADA's steady progress in commercialavionics, transportation, and factory automation systems, the prognosis isbetter.andM;&quot;As in any competitive industry however, those vendors that are forewarned,are forearmed, and are now ready to take advantage of current opportunities.&quot;andM;FAR bases is findings on its comprehensive market study &quot;Ada -- AnOpportunity Analysis,&quot; released to sponsoring organizations in 1990.andP;  Thestudy represents an information base of over 5,600 Ada programmers, with aninstalled base of 3,000 units of Ada development hardware valued atapproximately $243 million.andM;The study also includes projections and analysis resulting from interviewswith key Ada vendors, users, congressional staffers, and defense officials.andM;FAR has added a forward to the study, reflecting on recent events in the Adamarkets since the study's initial release.andM;&quot;In a lean market you can't afford to make strategic mistakes,&quot; said WesHair, product manager at Cadre Systems.andP;  &quot;In fact, there's oftenopportunities available due to the fallout in the market.andM;FAR's market analysis enabled us to forecast and plan for market shifts,while positioning ourselves for long-term opportunities.&quot;andM;The complete study, including detailed data base summary, is now generallyavailable and can be purchased for $845.andP;  The study is available through FARCorp., or International Data Corp.andM;For international pricing or more information, contact Dave Dikel at FAR,7799 Leesburg Pike, Suite 900, Falls Church, VA 22043, 703/847-6741, or703/356-2217 (fax).andO;</TEXT></DOC>